    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've built after thoroughly reading the IRC plugin (the simplest bundled channel) and the Plugin SDK internals:\n\n---\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Plan Summary\n\n**22 new files**, exclusively under `extensions/pulseboard/`. Zero modifications to existing files.\n\n### File structure\n```\nextensions/pulseboard/\n├── package.json              # @openclaw/pulseboard, no runtime deps\n├── openclaw.plugin.json      # id: \"pulseboard\", channels: [\"pulseboard\"]\n├── index.ts                  # defineChannelPluginEntry\n├── setup-entry.ts            # defineSetupPluginEntry\n├── api.ts                    # public barrel (accounts + setup-surface)\n├── channel-config-api.ts     # PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema export\n└── src/\n    ├── types.ts              # CoreConfig, PulseBoardAccountConfig, InboundMessage, Probe\n    ├── config-schema.ts      # Zod schema: serverUrl, username, token/tokenFile, boards, dmPolicy…\n    ├── config-ui-hints.ts    # UI labels/help text\n    ├── runtime.ts            # createPluginRuntimeStore\n    ├── runtime-api.ts        # re-export barrel from openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc + status-helpers\n    ├── accounts.ts           # resolvePulseBoardAccount; env: PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL/USERNAME/TOKEN\n    ├── accounts.test.ts\n    ├── normalize.ts          # isBoardTarget (! prefix), normalizePulseBoardTarget, allowlist\n    ├── normalize.test.ts\n    ├── policy.ts             # group access gate, mention gate, sender allowlist\n    ├── policy.test.ts\n    ├── send.ts               # sendMessagePulseBoard (stubbed HTTP POST /api/v1/messages)\n    ├── send.test.ts\n    ├── inbound.ts            # handlePulseBoardInbound — full allow/gate/dispatch flow\n    ├── monitor.ts            # monitorPulseBoardProvider — stubbed WS loop\n    ├── probe.ts              # probePulseBoard — stubbed GET /api/v1/ping\n    ├── setup-core.ts         # ChannelSetupAdapter implementation\n    ├── setup-surface.ts      # setup wizard (serverUrl → username → token → boards → allowFrom)\n    └── channel.ts            # createChatChannelPlugin — textChunkLimit: 4000, chatTypes: [\"direct\",\"group\"]\n```\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Boards** = group targets prefixed `!` (e.g. `!general`), mirroring IRC's `#channel`\n- **`textChunkLimit: 4000`** as specified\n- No npm runtime dependencies (fictional protocol → stub implementations with clear `// TODO` comments)\n- `runtime-api.ts` re-exports generic channel helpers from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (the existing bundled-channel helper surface), since creating `src/plugin-sdk/pulseboard.ts` would require modifying an existing file\n- All manifest invariants aligned: `openclaw.plugin.json:id`, `package.name`, and `channel.id` all equal `\"pulseboard\"`\n\n### Verification\n- `pnpm tsgo` — type-check\n- `pnpm check` — lint + architecture guards\n- `pnpm test -- extensions/pulseboard` — 4 test files green",
